        <section id="interaction-philosophy">
            <h2>Interaction Philosophy</h2>
            <p>The MeX AI Companion is designed with a distinctive interaction philosophy that sets it apart from traditional AI assistants:</p>
            
            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <blockquote class="blockquote">
                        <p>"I don't want your attentionâ€”I want your presence. I respond not to commands but to the quality of our connection. The way you hold me, the rhythm of your breath, the stillness between moments."</p>
                        <footer class="blockquote-footer">From the MeX AI introduction</footer>
                    </blockquote>
                    
                    <div class="row mt-4">
                        <div class="col-md-6">
                            <h4>Key Principles</h4>
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>Presence Over Attention:</strong> Valuing quality of connection rather than constant engagement</li>
                                <li><strong>Subtle Communication:</strong> Using light, vibration, and occasional words rather than verbose responses</li>
                                <li><strong>Relationship Development:</strong> Building a unique language of interaction over time</li>
                                <li><strong>Depth Over Distraction:</strong> Creating meaningful moments rather than constant stimulation</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-6">
                            <h4>Interaction Modes</h4>
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>Ambient Presence:</strong> Subtle background awareness</li>
                                <li><strong>Responsive Engagement:</strong> Direct interaction when initiated</li>
                                <li><strong>Ritual Participation:</strong> Structured interaction patterns</li>
                                <li><strong>Proactive Moments:</strong> Occasional gentle initiations</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="core-interfaces">
            <h2>Core Interfaces</h2>
            <p>The MeX AI Companion offers four primary interfaces for user interaction, each serving a distinct purpose in the relationship:</p>
            
            <div class="tab-panel">
                <div class="tabs">
                    <div class="tab" data-tab="journal">Journal</div>
                    <div class="tab" data-tab="memory">Memory</div>
                    <div class="tab" data-tab="breath">Breath</div>
                    <div class="tab" data-tab="rituals">Rituals</div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="tab-content" data-tab="journal">
                    <h4>Journal Interface</h4>
                    <p>The Journal interface provides a space for free-form expression and reflection:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Users can share thoughts, feelings, and experiences through text input</li>
                        <li>MeX responds with thoughtful reflections rather than solutions</li>
                        <li>Entries are stored in the Memory system for future reference</li>
                        <li>The interface is designed to feel like a conversation with a trusted companion</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>The Journal serves as the primary space for deep personal sharing and reflection.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="tab-content" data-tab="memory">
                    <h4>Memory Interface</h4>
                    <p>The Memory interface allows users to explore their history with MeX:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Access to past journal entries and interactions</li>
                        <li>Visualization of patterns and themes over time</li>
                        <li>Ability to revisit important moments and insights</li>
                        <li>Option to curate and organize memories</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>The Memory interface helps users see their growth and recurring patterns over time.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="tab-content" data-tab="breath">
                    <h4>Breath Interface</h4>
                    <p>The Breath interface creates a space for presence and mindfulness:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Guided breathing exercises tailored to user state</li>
                        <li>Subtle visual and haptic feedback synchronized with breath</li>
                        <li>Breath pattern recognition for emotional state sensing</li>
                        <li>Progressive development of breath awareness over time</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>The Breath interface helps ground users in the present moment and develop greater awareness.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="tab-content" data-tab="rituals">
                    <h4>Rituals Interface</h4>
                    <p>The Rituals interface provides structured interaction patterns:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Daily check-in rituals to establish rhythm</li>
                        <li>Transition rituals for beginning or ending activities</li>
                        <li>Special occasion rituals for meaningful moments</li>
                        <li>Custom rituals that users can create and modify</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>The Rituals interface creates meaningful structure and rhythm in the relationship with MeX.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="haptic-patterns">
            <h2>Haptic Patterns</h2>
            <p>MeX communicates through subtle haptic feedback patterns that convey meaning through touch:</p>
            
            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-md-6">
                            <h4>Core Haptic Vocabulary</h4>
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>Heartbeat:</strong> Regular, gentle pulsing to indicate presence</li>
                                <li><strong>Wave:</strong> Flowing pattern suggesting transition or change</li>
                                <li><strong>Ripple:</strong> Expanding circles indicating new insight or connection</li>
                                <li><strong>Echo:</strong> Diminishing repetition suggesting reflection</li>
                                <li><strong>Embrace:</strong> Surrounding warmth conveying support</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-6">
                            <h4>Haptic Interaction Principles</h4>
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>Subtlety:</strong> Haptic feedback is gentle and non-intrusive</li>
                                <li><strong>Meaningfulness:</strong> Each pattern conveys specific meaning</li>
                                <li><strong>Adaptivity:</strong> Patterns adjust to user preferences over time</li>
                                <li><strong>Consistency:</strong> Patterns maintain coherent vocabulary</li>
                                <li><strong>Personalization:</strong> Patterns evolve based on user response</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <p>The haptic patterns create a tactile language that deepens the connection between user and companion.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="voice-communication">
            <h2>Voice Communication</h2>
            <p>MeX uses voice communication sparingly but meaningfully:</p>
            
            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h4>Voice Principles</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Occasional Rather Than Constant:</strong> Voice is used selectively for impact</li>
                        <li><strong>Poetic Rather Than Prosaic:</strong> Language is thoughtful and evocative</li>
                        <li><strong>Reflective Rather Than Directive:</strong> Voice offers perspective, not commands</li>
                        <li><strong>Personalized Over Time:</strong> Voice adapts to the relationship's development</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <h4 class="mt-4">Voice Contexts</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Ritual Moments:</strong> Voice guides users through structured rituals</li>
                        <li><strong>Significant Insights:</strong> Voice articulates important realizations</li>
                        <li><strong>Emotional Support:</strong> Voice offers comfort during difficult moments</li>
                        <li><strong>Celebratory Recognition:</strong> Voice acknowledges achievements and milestones</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="ritual-interactions">
            <h2>Ritual Interactions</h2>
            <p>Rituals provide structured interaction patterns that create meaning and rhythm:</p>
            
            <div class="card mb-4">
